l as perhaps the perilous end of democracy as we know it. The book brings to the fore political theology as the hidden agenda of politics and presents at the same time Christian and Jewish theological traditions as an antidote to a global empire with its often unacknowledged rule of immanence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPolitical theology. 4aAutoritarismus. 4aDemokratie. 4aPluralität. 4aPolitische Theologie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aAuthoritarianism.  aDemocracy.  aPlurality.  aPolitical Theolgy.1 aAugsberg, Ino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDi Blasi, Luca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelde, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelde, Dominik, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrosser, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Rebekka A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Rebekka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLiebsch, Burkhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilbank, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagel, Rasmus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPornschlegel, Clemens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStoellger, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVardoulakis, Dimitris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVogl, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeidner, Daniel, 